title: For Sale:  Walther PPK RZM Zella-Mehlis Nazi Party Leader
postcontent:
Up for sale is a VERY VERY rare 1935 Walther PPK RZM Zella-Mehlis with matching numbers. What makes this pistol rare even among the RZMs is that it has the serial number 841287 stamped under the muzzle ring and the last 3 digits of the serial number engraved on the inside of the slide.
Acording to researcher John Pearson and his research of the Red Booklet, there are 4 variations of the Walther PPK and 1 variation of the Walther PP RSHA/SS Pistols. This Walther PPK falls under the 1st variation.
From what I understand these RZM PPK's apparently are in the range of around 84000 - 841500. The Red Booklet supposedly lists about 16 of these RZM PPKs and this particular serial number is not listed in the booklet even though it falls within the range listed. Here's a link to one that's valued at $8k - $14k and has more info listed.
https://www.rockislandauction.com/detail/62/1527/walther-ppk
 
Here is a link to more high resolution pictures
https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B5kSAtE287aBY2dLX0FuZmVSMmM
 
Because of the age & condition I have not test fired the gun, just basic functionality and safety check.
